e1: EMINT-Customer service takes a short-term view and engineering a long-term view.
e2: EMINT-It is difficult for engineers to communicate effectively with customer service staff.
e3: EMINT-Engineers and customer service staff cannot trust each other.
e4: EMINT-Engineers and customer service staff have different values.
e5: EMINT-Engineers and customer service staff do not understand each other.
e6: EMINT-Friction between engineers and customer service staff is healthy.
e7: EMINT-All engineers should know something about customer service.
e8: EMINT-Engineers are more important to a water utility than customer service staff.
p1: PROOR-Customers that cannot pay their bill have the wrong financial priorities.
p2: PROOR-Financial management is more important than the needs of individual customers that cannot afford water bills.
p3: PROOR-Customers who are not able to pay their bill do not need our help.
p4: PROOR-Customers who do not pay their bills on time should not receive service.
p5: PROOR-The more detailed our rules and regulations are, the better the level of service we will provide.
p6: PROOR-When we provide service in accordance with rules and regulations, customers will always be satisfied.
p7: PROOR-Decisions must be based on rules and regulations instead of individual customer needs.
p8: PROOR-Without detailed rules and regulations we are not able to provide satisfactory service to customers.
p9: PROOR-The more we invest in infrastructure maintenance and development, the more satisfied our customers will be.
p10: PROOR-Providing services is predominately a technological activity, not a customer support activity.
p11: PROOR-Customers do not have the knowledge to independently assess the level of service we provide.
p12: PROOR-Providing services in accordance with technical standards and regulations is sufficient to meet customer needs.
m1: MKTOR-Our business objectives are primarily driven by providing customer satisfaction.
m2: MKTOR-We constantly monitor our level of commitment and orientation to serving customer's needs.
m3: MKTOR-Our strategy is based on our understanding of customer needs.
m4: MKTOR-Our business strategies are driven by our beliefs about how we can provide greater value for customers.
m5: MKTOR-We measure customer satisfaction systematically and frequently.
m6: MKTOR-Our top managers from every function regularly meet with our customers.
m7: MKTOR-We freely communicate information about our successful and unsuccessful customer experiences across all business functions.
m8: MKTOR-All of our functions are integrated in serving the needs of our customers.
m9: MKTOR-Everybody understands how everyone in our business can contribute to creating customer value.
m10: MKTOR-We share resources with other business units.
